## ⚡ Quick Start

### 1. Infrastructure Setup
Start the required databases, message brokers, and sidecars:
```bash
docker-compose up -d
```
<% if (messagingQueue && queueType === 'Kafka') { %>
**Kafka Initialization:**
If you see `UNKNOWN_TOPIC_OR_PARTITION` errors on startup, your Kafka broker may not have auto-created the topics fast enough. You can manually create the required topics by running:
```bash
docker exec -it kafka /opt/kafka/bin/kafka-topics.sh --create --if-not-exists --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --partitions 1 --replication-factor 1 --topic <%= projectName %>.reply && \
docker exec -it kafka /opt/kafka/bin/kafka-topics.sh --create --if-not-exists --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --partitions 1 --replication-factor 1 --topic my-topic && \
docker exec -it kafka /opt/kafka/bin/kafka-topics.sh --create --if-not-exists --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --partitions 1 --replication-factor 1 --topic my-event
```
<% } %>

### 2. Environment Configuration
Initialize your environment variables:
```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

### 3. Start Development Server
```bash
<%= packageManager %> install
<%= packageManager %> run start:dev
```

